content.summary:
A part-to-whole chart is a rectangular graph that shows numerical proportion using blocks that have an area proportional to the quantity they represent. Part-to-whole charts are used to show relative comparisons between blocks as part of a total value.

This part-to-whole chart visualizes the data from the donut chart above it. An option was selected when creating this chart to display the summary below the chart.
